          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>    As you might have noticed, in presenting Dunn-Belnap valuations, I started from the Dunn-Belnap structure.
    That's how I'll continue to present different kinds of structures and valuations: by presenting the structure first.
    That determines what the valuations are: the different ways of assigning the values in the structure to the atomic sentences, extended to all sentences by following what the structure says about the connectives.
</html:p>
            <html:p>    Let's look now at the following structure, known as the <html:strong>strong Kleene</html:strong> structure, named after the logician Stephen Kleene:
</html:p>
